Self-custody is a key component of bitcoin s value proposition.   It is imperative that you learn how it works.  Whether you use Ledger or another provider, make sure you are educated.   Get the full value out of bitcoin. Become a self-custody bitcoiner.

Ledger s wallets work to store your private keys offline while being integrated to the Ledger Live apps which provide tools to buy, swap, sell, &amp  stake - become your own full service digital bank.   You can check out Ledger’s full suite of products here: https://t.co/SHaRLJANDC

You should do your own research and learn about self-custody.  I ve been working with @Ledger on the podcast for awhile now.  They are a company making bitcoin ownership easy, without ever sacrificing security or self-custody with their hardware wallets and Ledger Live products.

One of the safest ways to store your bitcoin is on a hardware wallet where your private keys are stored offline, in the device itself, eliminating the risks associated with online storage of your keys.   You don’t have to worry about your bitcoin getting stuck in an exchange.

The current bear market has shown us now, more than ever, just how true the expression “not your keys, not your coins!” actually is.   When you own the private keys to your bitcoin you are in full control.

It is crucial to understand that being your own bank is the most secure way to keep your bitcoin safe.  Especially when entering a space where centralized exchanges still have the authority to suspend crypto withdrawals and the risk of a hack is always looming.

As the mainstream enters bitcoin, they will flow to wherever the user experience is the friendliest when it comes to navigating self-custody over their assets.   Self-custody is one of the more intimidating sides of bitcoin.

Bitcoin is the most free market macro asset we have.  It went almost 1000% from Jan 2020 to Nov 2021.  It has come down 70% in anticipation of tighter financial conditions.  But bitcoin still up 300% since pre-pandemic.  Outperformed stocks, bonds, currencies, and commodities.

Market conditions are often, but not always, telegraphed.   Investors don’t wait for the conditions to materialize.  They move capital in anticipation so they can financially benefit.  There is a reason why “don’t fight the Fed” is a popular saying.

Many people are now yelling “why is bitcoin going down but inflation is high? Inflation hedge failed!”  Wrong.  Bitcoin and other assets are crashing in ANTICIPATION of inflation coming down.  Investors understand what the Fed is doing. They are moving in advance of the results.

When investors moved into inflation hedges, bitcoin was the big winner.  It went from ~$10,000 to ~ $60,000 in a matter of months.  Investors don’t wait for inflation to show up and then move capital.  They move in ANTICIPATION.

When COVID hit the US, central bankers and politicians stepped in with insane monetary and fiscal stimulus.  Smart investors realized inflation was essentially guaranteed.  These investors moved into inflation hedges in Q3/4 of 2020….BEFORE inflation showed up.
